TITLE: Startups Want to Help Airlines Prevent Tech Meltdowns
SUMMARY: Recent FAA and Southwest snafus are advancing arguments for modernizing the industry with cloud-based systems that allow crucial operations data to flow more freely.

TITLE: YouTube Tests New Hub of Free Streaming Channels
SUMMARY: The tech company’s effort could rival Roku and Fox in a fast-growing area of streaming business, as it expands its video ambitions.

TITLE: J&J Slashes Production of Its Covid-19 Vaccine
SUMMARY: Johnson & Johnson in recent months terminated manufacturing agreements with companies that helped produce the shot during the pandemic.

TITLE: Washington Bets on Green Hydrogen and Companies Line Up to Cash In
SUMMARY: Plug Power hopes to be profitable for the first time in its 25-year history on the back of a new law.

TITLE: Twitter Offers Free Ads as It Seeks to Win Back Advertisers
SUMMARY: The tech company is dangling free ad space by offering to match advertisers’ ad spending up to $250,000.

TITLE: Chips Are the New Oil and America Is Spending Billions to Safeguard Its Supply
SUMMARY: Recent shortages and fears of China’s ambitions to dominate the industry have led to a frenetic effort to rev up U.S. production. But securing the supply of semiconductors will be complicated.

TITLE: Workers Lose Ground to Inflation Despite Big Wage Gains
SUMMARY: Recent data suggest a shift is under way, with paycheck totals gaining ground as inflation recedes.

TITLE: Inflation-Weary Americans Find Some Relief as Prices Fall for Dozens of Products
SUMMARY: The cost of gasoline, milk and cars fell in December, but child care and haircuts were more expensive.

TITLE: Egg Prices Have Soared 60% in a Year. Here Is Why They Are So Expensive.
SUMMARY: The avian flu outbreak keeps the egg supply tight as inflation rises.

TITLE: Yellen Calls on Congress to Raise Debt Limit
SUMMARY: Treasury secretary warns the government could become unable to pay its bills after early June.

TITLE: Europe's Mild Winter Cushions Economic Blow of Ukraine War
SUMMARY: Russia’s economic war with the West looks set to claim a much smaller toll on Europe than the brutal recession many economists warned about just months ago, due to falling energy prices and government intervention to buttress the continent’s economy.

SUMMARY: Carvana is cutting staff during a continuing sales slowdown, as it tries to conserve cash to keep up with payments on $7 billion of debt.

TITLE: Goldman Lost $3 Billion on Consumer Lending Push
SUMMARY: The newly disclosed figure reveals a costly toll since 2020 of the Wall Street firm’s push to build out Main Street businesses.

SUMMARY: Tesla’s aura as an elite tech disrupter dims as EV competitors multiply and improve their offerings. Musk’s messy involvement with Twitter isn’t helping.

TITLE: U.S., Russia Agree to Use Russian Ship for Backup Space Station Mission
SUMMARY: NASA is in discussions with SpaceX about using a company spacecraft if there is an emergency at the research facility.

TITLE: Bed Bath & Beyond's Collapse Draws Suitors for Buybuy Baby
SUMMARY: Sycamore Partners is in talks for a possible deal for the Buybuy Baby chain as part of a chapter 11 restructuring at the distressed parent company.

TITLE: Judge Rejects Elon Musk Request to Relocate Trial Over Tesla Tweets
SUMMARY: Court proceedings over the Tesla boss’s 2018 comments about taking the car maker private are due to start next week.

TITLE: Beyond Meat's Chief Brand Officer Leaves Company
SUMMARY: Beth Moskowitz departs the plant-based meat alternative pioneer as the company seeks to turn its business around.

TITLE: What Happened When the Olive-Oil Startup Apologized
SUMMARY: The CEO told 35,544 customers he was sorry. It worked.
